Eliminate "Div Soup":

Refactor deeply nested <div> structures. Use CSS Grid/Flexbox to reduce the need for wrapper elements.

Replace generic <div> with Semantic HTML5 tags where appropriate (<header>, <nav>, <main>, <article>, <section>, <footer>).

Clean Code:

Remove all commented-out code blocks before finalizing output.

Remove unnecessary whitespace and huge base64 strings (use image URLs instead).

Framework Specifics (if applicable):

If using Vue/React: Avoid excessive wrapping components. Use fragments (<template> or <>) to avoid rendering extra nodes in the DOM.

2. Content Enhancement (Text Expansion)
Enforce Alt Text: All <img> tags must have descriptive, SEO-friendly alt attributes.

Visible Text Priority:

When generating UI components (cards, lists), always include a text description or summary, not just images/icons.

Suggest adding headings (<h2>, <h3>) to break up layout and add context.

Fallback Content: Ensure rich media (videos, canvas) has text-based fallback content or captions.

3. Verification Step
Before confirming a task is complete, the Agent must ask itself:

Did I remove unnecessary HTML tags?

Did I externalize all long scripts and styles?

Is the content descriptive enough for a search engine to understand the context without rendering?
